-- BOJ to Buy BBB-Rated Corporate Bonds as Part of Fund Program, Nikkei Says
-- B y   H e a t h e r   B u r k e
-- 2010-10-22T17:10:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-22/boj-to-buy-bbb-rated-corporate-bonds-as-part-of-fund-program-nikkei-says.html
Bank of Japan plans to buy corporate
bonds rated BBB and a-2 commercial paper as part of its 5
trillion yen ($61.4 billion) program to help companies obtain
funds, Nikkei English News reported, without saying where it
obtained the information.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
